{
  "name": "Living Steel",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "modules/pf1spheres/assets/icons/spheres/nature.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Nature sphere ((metal) package, (plant) package), caster level 5th.</p>\n<p>As an instantaneous effect, you may as a standard action spend 2 spell points to permanently grant the effects of living steel to a metal creature or object whose size is no larger than the ore that you may recover. Living steel repairs damage to itself at a rate of 2 hit points per day, or 1 hit point per day if it has the broken condition. In addition whenever the wielder of a metal weapon rolls a natural 1 on an attack roll against a creature wearing living steel armor or wielding a living steel shield, the item must succeed at a DC 20 Fortitude save or gain the broken condition. If the weapon already has the broken condition, it is instead destroyed. Living steel cannot damage adamantine weapons in this way.</p>\n",
